name: LED Dimmable Drivers
description:

Encased in a low profile aluminum enclosure that includes 2 knock-outs to enable easy installation makes it the perfect choice for under cabinet lights, tape lights and various LED fixtures installations. Our electrical specification includes Auto Reset, over current and short circuit protection, and efficiency of 90% and higher allows the driver to operate at low temperatures. Offered in a variety of wattages in both 12V and 24V DC models.

Check the instructions tab for a compatible Dimmer list. The listed Dimmers were tested with our LED Drivers. Dimmer performance may vary within the same model or with different LED load types. Additional MLV (Magnetic Low Voltage) dimmers may be used. Please contact Customer Service for details.

name: LED Non Dimmable Drivers
description: A LED driver is an electrical device that regulates the power to an LED or string(s) of LEDs. What makes a driver different from conventional power supplies is that an LED driver responds to the ever-changing needs of the LED, or circuit of LEDs, by supplying a constant amount of power to the LED as its electrical properties change with temperature. Non-Dimmable Drivers provide steady 12V or 24V current along with high efficiency. All our LED drivers are energy-efficient, eco-friendly, safe, and produce very little heat. We offer a wide varirty of hard-wired and portable drivers for wall or ceiling, in attic or under counters, but also compact enough for areas with limited space. Available in both Indoor and Outdoor designs.

name: RGB/RGBW CCT & Dimming Controllers
description: RGB Stands for "Red Green Blue." It refers to the three hues of light that can mix together to form any color. When the highest intensity of each color is mixed together, white light is created. When you use RGB Color Changing LED Lights, you no longer have to decide which color to use. You can either allow the lights to cycle through a continuous color changing pattern, or stop the controller at any color you like. The possibilities are endless. Change your color scheme with the seasons, or simply at a whim with RGB Color changing controllers like our simple and easy to use LT-09S-RF Controller & Dimmer with handheld RF Touch Color Remote or our LN-CON-WiFi-3CH-XV WiFi Controller with mobile apps to control dynamic lighting inside a house, bar, office block, shopping center, hotel or even a landmark.

name: Transformers
description: A transformer is an electrical device that transfers energy between two circuits through electromagnetic induction. Transformer are used as a safe and efficient voltage converter to change the AC voltage at its input to a higher or lower voltage at its output. NSL offers a wide range of transformer designs for both electronic and magnetic, indoor/outdoor applications.

name: CENSE
description:
The CENSE Central Driver System is an integrated multi-zone DC powered control panel for high power LED lighting applications. CENSE offers a multitude of control protocols forcontrol and dimming while also incorporating an industryleading power control system to deliver up to 98% efficientLED output.

With independent channels, CENSE caters to the needs ofnumerous DC LED Lighting applications, including commercial,industrial, residential, multi-dwelling, recreational vehicle,marine and so much more. CENSE operates from DC inputvoltage and is both flexible and capable with a total of 8 LM1 units per system.?

name: Neo
description:
Neo, our energy storage platform, is a core element of our control system and can provide power when hydro goes down. With the low voltage requirements of our lighting system this can mean additional days of light when you really need it. You’ll never be suddenly left in the dark again.

Charged from a renewable energy source or by the utility grid, Neo runs your lights 24/7 and can protect you against power outages by providing backup electricity for your iLLUMA-Drive lighting platform and essential loads. Power goes out, lights and devices stay on.

Paired with a renewable energy source (typically solar), Neo provides increased independence because all of your lighting needs will be powered by your system even when the power grid has service interruptions.

name: SWITCHEX
description: SWITCHEX simplifies LED array lighting systems by combining an inwall LED dimmer switch and power supply into a single integrated unit.SWITCHEX mounts in a standard in-wall switch box, accepts 120V AC and converts to low voltage DC. SWITCHEX is compatible with 2-channel 12V and 24VDC tape light and constant voltage fixtures.

name: DMX Controllers
description: DMX (Digital Multiplex) is a standard for digital communication networks that are commonly used to control stage lighting and effects. It was originally intended as a standardized method for controlling light dimmers dedicated to what we call architectural installations, but has expanded to uses in non-theatrical interior and architectural lighting, at scales ranging from strings of Christmas lights to electronic billboards. DMX can now be used to control almost anything,  from the basic 128 STICK-GU2 with output channels to the sophisticated STICK-DE3 with 1024 DMX output channels and the ability to store 500 scenes across 10 zones and literally more than 16,000,000 possibilities with computer software and mobile apps. Once integrated with the compatible software packages, it is possible to easily control the lighting within a variety of places such as homes, hotels, restaurants, fountains, gardens, commercial and many more.??

name: LED Panel Lights
description:
LED Panel Lights are designed for residential and commercial suspended grid ceilings in 1'x4', 2'x2' and 2'x4' sizes. LED Panel Lights are used for office lighting, basement lighting, light box and sign back-lighting, gym lighting, school lighting, hospital lighting, and more!

Replace existing fluorescent troffer light fixtures or use for new construction applications. LED Panel Lights deliver a smooth, flawless wall of illumination without visible bulbs or hot spots. Bright and powerful—the DLC 4.0 Standard series with 100 - 120lm/watt and the DLC 4.0 Premium with 125 -140lm/watt and output of up to 7,800 lumens. Available in 3000K, 4000K and 5000K color temperatures. The energy-efficient, cULus Listed LED panel operates within a wide 120-277V AC range, has a sturdy anodized aluminum alloy frame with white finish and 3mm PMMA, Anti-yellowing lens. Each panel includes a UL-Recognized constant-current driver with 0-10V dimming and terminal block connections of easy installations. Mount with our LED Panel Light Suspension Kit, Surface mount Kit or in an existing compatible location.
